Section 1:
1 L.D. 839
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 ENERGY, UTILITIES AND TECHNOLOGY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 372, L.D. 839, “An Act to Lower
10 Consumer Electricity Costs by Prohibiting the Recovery Through Rates of Costs
11 Attributable to Net Energy Billing”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Create the Net Energy Billing Cost Stabilization Fund'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 35-A MRSA §3209-F is enacted to read:
17 §3209-F. Net Energy Billing Cost Stabilization Fund
18 1. Fund established. There is established the Net Energy Billing Cost Stabilization
19 Fund, referred to in this section as "the fund," as an account within the commission. The
20 fund is a nonlapsing, revolving fund administered by the commission for the purpose of
21 offsetting the costs to ratepayers associated with the net energy billing program under
22 section 3209-A and section 3209-B.
23 2. Sources for fund. The commission may receive and deposit in the fund funds from
24 the following sources:
25 A. Federal funds and awards that may be used for the purposes specified in this section;
26 B. Appropriations and transfers authorized by the Legislature; and
27 C. Any other funds from public or private sources received for the purposes of this
28 section.
29 3. Use of funds. To the extent that funds are available, the commission shall use the
30 fund exclusively to make payments to reimburse transmission and distribution utilities for
31 any costs incurred as a result of the net energy billing program under section 3209-A and
32 section 3209-B that would have otherwise been paid by ratepayers.
Page 1 - 132LR0706(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 372, L.D. 839
1 4. Rules. The commission may adopt rules to implement this section. Rules adopted
2 pursuant to this subsection are routine technical rules as defined in Title 5, chapter 375,
3 subchapter 2‑A.
4 5. Report. By February 1st of any year in which the commission has paid a
5 reimbursement from the fund to a transmission and distribution utility in the prior calendar
6 year, the commission shall provide a report to the joint standing committee of the
7 Legislature having jurisdiction over electricity matters that includes the amount of the
8 reimbursement paid in the prior calendar year, the source of any funds received by the fund
9 in the prior calendar year and any other relevant information as determined by the
10 commission. The committee may report out a bill related to the commission's report.
11 Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
12 allocations are made.
13 PUBLIC UTILITIES COMMISSION
14 Net Energy Billing Cost Stabilization Fund N540
15 Initiative: Provides one-time funding for the purpose of making payments to transmission
16 and distribution utilities that would have otherwise been paid by ratepayers.
17 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
18 All Other $500 $0
19 __________ __________
20 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $500 $0
2117 '
22 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
23 number to read consecutively.
24 SUMMARY
2255 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. It establishes the Net Energy
2266 Billing Cost Stabilization Fund within the Public Utilities Commission. It provides that the
2277 fund must be used to reimburse a transmission and distribution utility for any costs incurred
2288 as a result of the State's net energy billing programs that would have otherwise been paid
2299 by ratepayers. It requires the commission to submit to the joint standing committee of the
3300 Legislature having jurisdiction over electricity matters a report that includes information
3311 about funds received by the fund and used for reimbursements for any year in which the
3322 commission pays reimbursements through the fund. It authorizes the commission to adopt
3333 rules to implement the requirements of the legislation. It includes a $500 appropriation for
3344 the Net Energy Billing Cost Stabilization Fund.
3355 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3366 (See attached)
